{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":817,"text":"I'm assuming everyone here has watched"},{"time":2177,"text":"a TED Talk online at one time or another, right?"},{"time":6541,"text":"So what I'm going to do is play this."},{"time":8643,"text":"This is the song from the TED Talks online."},{"time":11494,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":18249,"text":"And I'm going to slow it down"},{"time":19540,"text":"because things sound cooler when they're slower."},{"time":22321,"text":"(Music)"},{"time":66683,"text":"Ken Robinson: Good morning. How are you?"},{"time":70348,"text":"Mark Applebaum: I'm going to --\nKate Stone: -- mix some music."},{"time":73688,"text":"MA: I'm going to do so in a way that tells a story."},{"time":75794,"text":"Tod Machover: Something nobody's ever heard before."},{"time":78905,"text":"KS: I have a crossfader."},{"time":80399,"text":"Julian Treasure: I call this the mixer."},{"time":82048,"text":"KS: Two D.J. decks."},{"time":83348,"text":"Chris Anderson: You turn up the \ndials, the wheel starts to turn."},{"time":90571,"text":"Dan Ellsey: I have always loved music."},{"time":92953,"text":"Michael Tilson Thomas: Is it a melody \nor a rhythm or a mood or an attitude?"},{"time":95468,"text":"Daniel Wolpert: Feeling everything \nthat's going on inside my body."},{"time":98124,"text":"Adam Ockelford: In your brain is \nthis amazing musical computer."},{"time":104002,"text":"MTT: Using computers and synthesizers to create \nworks. It's a language that's still evolving."},{"time":115647,"text":"And the 21st century."},{"time":118074,"text":"KR: Turn on the radio. Pop into the discotheque."},{"time":120712,"text":"You will know what this person \nis doing: moving to the music."},{"time":135610,"text":"Mark Ronson: This is my favorite part."},{"time":137982,"text":"MA: You gotta have doorstops. That's important."},{"time":142197,"text":"TM: We all love music a great deal."},{"time":143884,"text":"MTT: Anthems, dance crazes, ballads and marches."},{"time":147044,"text":"Kirby Ferguson and JT: The remix: It \nis new music created from old music."},{"time":150767,"text":"Ryan Holladay: Blend seamlessly."},{"time":153028,"text":"Kathryn Schulz: And that's how it goes."},{"time":154483,"text":"MTT: What happens when the music stops?"},{"time":161918,"text":"KS: Yay!"},{"time":165684,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":171594,"text":"MR: Obviously, I've been watching a lot of TED Talks."},{"time":176124,"text":"When I was first asked to speak at TED,"},{"time":179503,"text":"I wasn't quite sure what my angle was, at first,"},{"time":181516,"text":"so yeah, I immediately started\nwatching tons of TED Talks,"},{"time":184468,"text":"which is pretty much absolutely"},{"time":186484,"text":"the worst thing that you can do"},{"time":188323,"text":"because you start to go into panic mode, thinking,"},{"time":191151,"text":"I haven't mounted a successful\nexpedition to the North Pole yet."},{"time":194652,"text":"Neither have I provided electricity"},{"time":198552,"text":"to my village through sheer ingenuity."},{"time":201149,"text":"In fact, I've pretty much wasted most of my life"},{"time":203969,"text":"DJing in night clubs"},{"time":205266,"text":"and producing pop records."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207245,"text":"But I still kept watching the videos,"},{"time":209920,"text":"because I'm a masochist,"},{"time":211551,"text":"and eventually, things like Michael Tilson Thomas"},{"time":214623,"text":"and Tod Machover, and seeing"},{"time":217439,"text":"their visceral passion talking about music,"},{"time":219606,"text":"it definitely stirred something in me,"},{"time":221433,"text":"and I'm a sucker for anyone talking devotedly"},{"time":223778,"text":"about the power of music."},{"time":225169,"text":"And I started to write down on these little note cards"},{"time":227829,"text":"every time I heard something"},{"time":229172,"text":"that struck a chord in me, pardon the pun,"},{"time":231387,"text":"or something that I thought I could use,"},{"time":233143,"text":"and pretty soon, my studio looked like this,"},{"time":237810,"text":"kind of like a John Nash, \"Beautiful Mind\" vibe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241573,"text":"The other good thing about watching TED Talks,"},{"time":244368,"text":"when you see a really good one,"},{"time":246255,"text":"you kind of all of a sudden wish the speaker"},{"time":248188,"text":"was your best friend, don't you? Like, just for a day."},{"time":251032,"text":"They seem like a nice person."},{"time":253027,"text":"You'd take a bike ride, maybe share an ice cream."},{"time":256009,"text":"You'd certainly learn a lot."},{"time":258760,"text":"And every now and then they'd chide you,"},{"time":260214,"text":"when they got frustrated that you couldn't really"},{"time":261950,"text":"keep up with half of the technical things\nthey're banging on about all the time."},{"time":264879,"text":"But then they'd remember that\nyou're but a mere human"},{"time":267348,"text":"of ordinary, mortal intelligence"},{"time":268830,"text":"that didn't finish university,"},{"time":270229,"text":"and they'd kind of forgive you,"},{"time":271795,"text":"and pet you like the dog."},{"time":275390,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":277515,"text":"Man, yeah, back to the real world,"},{"time":280253,"text":"probably Sir Ken Robinson and I"},{"time":281780,"text":"are not going to end up being best of friends."},{"time":283484,"text":"He lives all the way in L.A.\nand I imagine is quite busy,"},{"time":286917,"text":"but through the tools available to me -- technology"},{"time":289654,"text":"and the innate way that I approach making music --"},{"time":291922,"text":"I can sort of bully our existences"},{"time":294660,"text":"into a shared event,"},{"time":295971,"text":"which is sort of what you saw."},{"time":298537,"text":"I can hear something that I love in a piece of media"},{"time":301546,"text":"and I can co-opt it"},{"time":302930,"text":"and insert myself in that narrative,"},{"time":305266,"text":"or alter it, even."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308238,"text":"In a nutshell, that's what I was trying to do"},{"time":309968,"text":"with these things, but more importantly,"},{"time":312174,"text":"that's what the past 30 years of music has been."},{"time":314564,"text":"That's the major thread."},{"time":316252,"text":"See, 30 years ago, you had the first digital samplers,"},{"time":318975,"text":"and they changed everything overnight."},{"time":320460,"text":"All of a sudden, artists could sample"},{"time":322125,"text":"from anything and everything that came before them,"},{"time":324930,"text":"from a snare drum from the Funky Meters,"},{"time":327125,"text":"to a Ron Carter bassline,"},{"time":328939,"text":"the theme to \"The Price Is Right.\""},{"time":331010,"text":"Albums like De La Soul's \"3 Feet High and Rising\""},{"time":333143,"text":"and the Beastie Boys' \"Paul's Boutique\""},{"time":335297,"text":"looted from decades of recorded music"},{"time":337555,"text":"to create these sonic, layered masterpieces"},{"time":340604,"text":"that were basically the Sgt. Peppers of their day."},{"time":342856,"text":"And they weren't sampling these records"},{"time":345503,"text":"because they were too lazy to write their own music."},{"time":348312,"text":"They weren't sampling these records to cash in on"},{"time":350277,"text":"the familiarity of the original stuff."},{"time":351946,"text":"To be honest, it was all about sampling"},{"time":353503,"text":"really obscure things,"},{"time":355044,"text":"except for a few obvious exceptions"},{"time":356532,"text":"like Vanilla Ice and \"doo doo doo da da doo doo\""},{"time":359361,"text":"that we know about."},{"time":360770,"text":"But the thing is,"},{"time":362205,"text":"they were sampling those records"},{"time":363680,"text":"because they heard something in that music"},{"time":365478,"text":"that spoke to them"},{"time":367643,"text":"that they instantly wanted to inject themselves"},{"time":369641,"text":"into the narrative of that music."},{"time":371137,"text":"They heard it, they wanted to be a part of it,"},{"time":372907,"text":"and all of a sudden they found themselves"},{"time":374501,"text":"in possession of the technology to do so,"},{"time":377160,"text":"not much unlike the way the Delta blues"},{"time":379351,"text":"struck a chord with the Stones\nand the Beatles and Clapton,"},{"time":382020,"text":"and they felt the need to co-opt that music"},{"time":384310,"text":"for the tools of their day."},{"time":386070,"text":"You know, in music we take something that we love"},{"time":388702,"text":"and we build on it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390120,"text":"I'd like to play a song for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400068,"text":"(Music: \"La Di Da Di\" by Doug E. Fresh &amp; Slick Rick)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419139,"text":"That's \"La Di Da Di\" and it's the fifth-most sampled"},{"time":421728,"text":"song of all time."},{"time":423032,"text":"It's been sampled 547 times."},{"time":426202,"text":"It was made in 1984 by these two legends of hip-hop,"},{"time":429638,"text":"Slick Rick and Doug E. Fresh,"},{"time":432817,"text":"and the Ray-Ban and Jheri curl look is so strong."},{"time":436227,"text":"I do hope that comes back soon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438255,"text":"Anyway, this predated the sampling era."},{"time":442348,"text":"There were no samples in this record,"},{"time":443850,"text":"although I did look up on the Internet last night,"},{"time":446206,"text":"I mean several months ago,"},{"time":448254,"text":"that \"La Di Da Di\" means, it's an old"},{"time":450779,"text":"Cockney expression from the late 1800s in England,"},{"time":453819,"text":"so maybe a remix with Mrs. Patmore"},{"time":455935,"text":"from \"Downton Abbey\" coming soon,"},{"time":457861,"text":"or that's for another day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":461445,"text":"Doug E. Fresh was the human beat box."},{"time":463171,"text":"Slick Rick is the voice you hear on the record,"},{"time":464955,"text":"and because of Slick Rick's sing-songy,"},{"time":468015,"text":"super-catchy vocals, it provides endless sound bites"},{"time":470804,"text":"and samples for future pop records."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473546,"text":"That was 1984."},{"time":474876,"text":"This is me in 1984, in case you were wondering"},{"time":477779,"text":"how I was doing, thank you for asking."},{"time":480310,"text":"It's Throwback Thursday already."},{"time":482411,"text":"I was involved in a heavy love affair"},{"time":484764,"text":"with the music of Duran Duran,"},{"time":486093,"text":"as you can probably tell from my outfit."},{"time":488164,"text":"I was in the middle."},{"time":489818,"text":"And the simplest way that I knew"},{"time":491949,"text":"how to co-opt myself into that experience"},{"time":494530,"text":"of wanting to be in that song somehow"},{"time":496463,"text":"was to just get a band together\nof fellow nine-year-olds"},{"time":498884,"text":"and play \"Wild Boys\" at the school talent show."},{"time":501391,"text":"So that's what we did, and long story short,"},{"time":503880,"text":"we were booed off the stage,"},{"time":505622,"text":"and if you ever have a chance to live your life"},{"time":508435,"text":"escaping hearing the sound of an auditorium"},{"time":510976,"text":"full of second- and third-graders booing,"},{"time":512529,"text":"I would highly recommend it. It's not really fun."},{"time":515137,"text":"But it didn't really matter,"},{"time":516437,"text":"because what I wanted somehow"},{"time":518205,"text":"was to just be in the history\nof that song for a minute."},{"time":520932,"text":"I didn't care who liked it."},{"time":522123,"text":"I just loved it, and I thought\nI could put myself in there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525442,"text":"Over the next 10 years, \"La Di Da Di\""},{"time":527210,"text":"continues to be sampled by countless records,"},{"time":529155,"text":"ending up on massive hits like\n\"Here Comes the Hotstepper\""},{"time":532879,"text":"and \"I Wanna Sex You Up.\""},{"time":534360,"text":"Snoop Doggy Dogg covers this song"},{"time":536241,"text":"on his debut album \"Doggystyle\"\nand calls it \"Lodi Dodi.\""},{"time":540304,"text":"Copyright lawyers are having\na field day at this point."},{"time":542712,"text":"And then you fast forward to 1997,"},{"time":545480,"text":"and the Notorious B.I.G., or Biggie,"},{"time":548334,"text":"reinterprets \"La Di Da Di\""},{"time":551296,"text":"on his number one hit called \"Hypnotize,\""},{"time":554104,"text":"which I will play a little bit of"},{"time":555626,"text":"and I will play you a little bit of the Slick Rick"},{"time":557208,"text":"to show you where they got it from."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560277,"text":"(Music: \"Hypnotize\" by The Notorious B.I.G.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587385,"text":"So Biggie was killed"},{"time":591372,"text":"weeks before that song made it to number one,"},{"time":593376,"text":"in one of the great tragedies of the hip-hop era,"},{"time":595578,"text":"but he would have been 13 years old"},{"time":597294,"text":"and very much alive when\n\"La Di Da Di\" first came out,"},{"time":599603,"text":"and as a young boy"},{"time":600865,"text":"growing up in Brooklyn,"},{"time":602516,"text":"it's hard not to think that that song probably held"},{"time":604658,"text":"some fond memories for him."},{"time":606089,"text":"But the way he interpreted it, as you hear,"},{"time":607875,"text":"is completely his own."},{"time":609290,"text":"He flips it, makes it,"},{"time":611365,"text":"there's nothing pastiche whatsoever about it."},{"time":613721,"text":"It's thoroughly modern Biggie."},{"time":616529,"text":"I had to make that joke in this room,"},{"time":618257,"text":"because you would be the only people\nthat I'd ever have a chance of getting it."},{"time":621083,"text":"And so, it's a groaner. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":624323,"text":"Elsewhere in the pop and rap world,"},{"time":627876,"text":"we're going a little bit sample-crazy."},{"time":629792,"text":"We're getting away from the obscure\nsamples that we were doing,"},{"time":632290,"text":"and all of a sudden everyone's taking"},{"time":633626,"text":"these massive '80s tunes like Bowie, \"Let's Dance,\""},{"time":636437,"text":"and all these disco records,\nand just rapping on them."},{"time":638816,"text":"These records don't really age that well."},{"time":640660,"text":"You don't hear them now, because they borrowed"},{"time":642715,"text":"from an era that was too steeped"},{"time":644309,"text":"in its own connotation."},{"time":646257,"text":"You can't just hijack nostalgia wholesale."},{"time":650969,"text":"It leaves the listener feeling sickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653093,"text":"You have to take an element of those things"},{"time":655356,"text":"and then bring something fresh and new to it,"},{"time":658235,"text":"which was something that I learned"},{"time":659425,"text":"when I was working with the late,"},{"time":661143,"text":"amazing Amy Winehouse"},{"time":662455,"text":"on her album \"Back to Black.\""},{"time":664696,"text":"A lot of fuss was made about the sonic of the album"},{"time":667752,"text":"that myself and Salaam Remi, the other producer,"},{"time":669781,"text":"achieved, how we captured this long-lost sound,"},{"time":671669,"text":"but without the very, very 21st-century personality"},{"time":675444,"text":"and firebrand that was Amy Winehouse"},{"time":677397,"text":"and her lyrics about rehab and Roger Moore"},{"time":680550,"text":"and even a mention of Slick Rick,"},{"time":682476,"text":"the whole thing would have run the risk"},{"time":683761,"text":"of being very pastiche, to be honest."},{"time":687222,"text":"Imagine any other singer from that era over it"},{"time":689510,"text":"singing the same old lyrics."},{"time":692201,"text":"It runs a risk of being completely bland."},{"time":694338,"text":"I mean, there was no doubt that Amy"},{"time":696851,"text":"and I and Salaam all had this love"},{"time":698809,"text":"for this gospel, soul and blues and jazz"},{"time":700599,"text":"that was evident listening to\nthe musical arrangements."},{"time":703818,"text":"She brought the ingredients that made it urgent"},{"time":705862,"text":"and of the time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707521,"text":"So if we come all the way up to the present day now,"},{"time":710558,"text":"the cultural tour de force that is Miley Cyrus,"},{"time":714070,"text":"she reinterprets \"La Di Da Di\""},{"time":716292,"text":"completely for her generation,"},{"time":718454,"text":"and we'll take a listen to the Slick Rick part"},{"time":721398,"text":"and then see how she sort of flipped it."},{"time":726309,"text":"(Music: \"La Di Da Di\" by Slick Rick &amp; Doug E. Fresh)"},{"time":739953,"text":"(Music: \"We Can't Stop\" by Miley Cyrus)"},{"time":745936,"text":"So Miley Cyrus,"},{"time":747777,"text":"who wasn't even born yet\nwhen \"La Di Da Di\" was made,"},{"time":751315,"text":"and neither were any of the co-writers on the song,"},{"time":754849,"text":"has found this song that somehow"},{"time":756959,"text":"etched its way into the collective\nconsciousness of pop music,"},{"time":760004,"text":"and now, with its timeless playfulness of the original,"},{"time":763957,"text":"has kind of translated to a whole new generation"},{"time":766380,"text":"who will probably co-opt it as their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770048,"text":"Since the dawn of the sampling era,"},{"time":773250,"text":"there's been endless debate"},{"time":774771,"text":"about the validity of music that contains samples."},{"time":777369,"text":"You know, the Grammy committee says that"},{"time":778995,"text":"if your song contains some kind of pre-written"},{"time":781653,"text":"or pre-existing music,"},{"time":782898,"text":"you're ineligible for song of the year."},{"time":784893,"text":"Rockists, who are racist"},{"time":787170,"text":"but only about rock music,"},{"time":788920,"text":"constantly use the argument to —"},{"time":793151,"text":"That's a real word. That is a real word."},{"time":795173,"text":"They constantly use the argument to devalue rap"},{"time":797789,"text":"and modern pop,"},{"time":799699,"text":"and these arguments completely miss the point,"},{"time":803861,"text":"because the dam has burst."},{"time":805820,"text":"We live in the post-sampling era."},{"time":807853,"text":"We take the things that we love"},{"time":809480,"text":"and we build on them."},{"time":810858,"text":"That's just how it goes."},{"time":812498,"text":"And when we really add\nsomething significant and original"},{"time":815590,"text":"and we merge our musical journey with this,"},{"time":818087,"text":"then we have a chance to be"},{"time":819925,"text":"a part of the evolution of that music that we love"},{"time":822558,"text":"and be linked with it once it\nbecomes something new again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825799,"text":"So I would like to do one more piece"},{"time":831163,"text":"that I put together for you tonight,"},{"time":832881,"text":"and it takes place with two"},{"time":835236,"text":"pretty inspiring TED performances that I've seen."},{"time":838272,"text":"One of them is the piano player Derek Paravicini,"},{"time":841907,"text":"who happens to be a blind,"},{"time":843989,"text":"autistic genius at the piano,"},{"time":845527,"text":"and Emmanuel Jal, who is an ex-child soldier"},{"time":847940,"text":"from the South Sudan,"},{"time":849260,"text":"who is a spoken word poet and rapper."},{"time":852122,"text":"And once again I found a way to annoyingly"},{"time":854460,"text":"me-me-me myself into the musical history"},{"time":856721,"text":"of these songs,"},{"time":859235,"text":"but I can't help it,"},{"time":860343,"text":"because they're these things that I love,"},{"time":862048,"text":"and I want to mess around with them."},{"time":863975,"text":"So I hope you enjoy this. Here we go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867712,"text":"Let's hear that TED sound again, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":869793,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":991423,"text":"Thank you very much. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994448,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}